10/02/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The ministry for diaspora announced on Tuesday (February 9th) that Serbs in Slovakia have been given national minority status.
The designation protects national minorities under international law and inter-state agreements.
Minister Srdjan Sreckovic says the decision will protect the Serbian community from all forms of discrimination.
(Tanjug, Medjunarodni Radio Srbija, RTS - 09/02/10)
